WEBVTT

00:00:12.240 --> 00:00:14.570
<i>The horse girls have moved to the gates.</i>

00:00:15.110 --> 00:00:17.580
<i>Today's race is special.</i>

00:00:19.850 --> 00:00:20.980
Yes, it is.

00:00:20.980 --> 00:00:22.460
There's someone to watch out there.

00:00:22.920 --> 00:00:24.680
<i>Yes, Silence Suzuka.</i>

00:00:24.680 --> 00:00:27.960
<i>Silence Suzuka is racing again.</i>

00:00:35.860 --> 00:00:38.480
<i>It's been a year and a
month since the accident.</i>

00:00:38.480 --> 00:00:42.930
<i>Will Silence Suzuka be
able to make a comeback?</i>

00:00:45.250 --> 00:00:46.940
{\an9}Broye

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:54.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

00:01:07.720 --> 00:01:12.940
Do you hear the fanfare as
we race towards the finish?

00:01:12.940 --> 00:01:19.470
I want to see that shining future with you

00:01:21.510 --> 00:01:27.810
{\an8}Umamusume

00:01:23.390 --> 00:01:27.690
{\an8}Pretty Derby

00:01:29.700 --> 00:01:35.420
If we just start to run, that's
where our story will begin

00:01:35.420 --> 00:01:40.440
It's always waiting right in front of us

00:01:40.440 --> 00:01:46.050
If you reach out just a little
more, we can seize that glory

00:01:46.050 --> 00:01:52.910
Aim for the top, challenge
them all, and it's off to the races

00:01:53.720 --> 00:01:58.910
Even the goddess of victory will be dazzled

00:01:58.910 --> 00:02:06.190
By your big debut that's just around the bend

00:02:06.190 --> 00:02:11.610
So can you hear the fanfare
as we race towards the finish?

00:02:11.610 --> 00:02:17.080
I want to see that shining future with you

00:02:17.080 --> 00:02:22.590
Let's overtake them all! It's
a track laid out just for you!

00:02:22.590 --> 00:02:30.350
Your dreams are at the finish if you believe

00:02:32.000 --> 00:02:36.010
{\an8}Race 11

00:02:32.000 --> 00:02:36.010
{\an8}Welcome Back!

00:02:46.890 --> 00:02:49.620
They sure are getting into this.

00:02:49.620 --> 00:02:53.650
They've always been serious, unlike you.

00:02:54.680 --> 00:02:57.400
Suzuka-senpai has her comeback race.

00:02:58.310 --> 00:02:59.810
That's enough staring.

00:02:59.810 --> 00:03:01.530
We gotta get going, too.

00:03:01.530 --> 00:03:02.160
Right!

00:03:02.570 --> 00:03:07.030
{\an8}1… 2…

00:03:03.620 --> 00:03:08.250
They've turned into a great team,
helping each other reach new heights.

00:03:08.250 --> 00:03:09.790
Team Spica!

00:03:12.000 --> 00:03:13.250
Tazuna-san?

00:03:13.290 --> 00:03:16.130
{\an9}Hayakawa Tazuna

00:03:13.560 --> 00:03:16.130
The school is in an uproar!

00:03:18.870 --> 00:03:23.260
Broye-san, is it true that you're
going to enter the Japan Cup?

00:03:25.250 --> 00:03:27.850
Yes, I will.

00:03:30.500 --> 00:03:32.480
Broye's going to enter the Japan Cup.

00:03:32.480 --> 00:03:33.350
Looking for a fight?

00:03:33.350 --> 00:03:36.140
Special Week's going to be
in the Japan Cup, right?

00:03:36.140 --> 00:03:36.730
Yes.

00:03:37.590 --> 00:03:39.110
Spe-chan…

00:03:41.370 --> 00:03:43.860
You took first in the Prix de
l'Arc de Triomphe, correct?

00:03:43.860 --> 00:03:45.990
Why would you take part in the Japan Cup?

00:03:46.220 --> 00:03:47.720
{\an8}I want to show everyone

00:03:48.390 --> 00:03:50.270
{\an8}what it really means to be strong!!

00:03:53.430 --> 00:03:56.920
Spe, you won't be able to rest for a while.

00:03:56.920 --> 00:03:58.010
Right!

00:03:58.670 --> 00:04:01.920
Broye's going to enter the Japan Cup!

00:04:01.920 --> 00:04:04.610
She's the one that even
El-senpai couldn't beat, right?

00:04:04.610 --> 00:04:07.510
Suzuka-senpai's comeback race is
going to happen the day before, too!

00:04:08.040 --> 00:04:09.610
I really want to see that!

00:04:09.610 --> 00:04:10.930
But—

00:04:13.690 --> 00:04:15.150
She's so wonderful.

00:04:15.150 --> 00:04:16.190
Suzuka!

00:04:16.530 --> 00:04:17.690
Good morning.

00:04:17.690 --> 00:04:19.400
Good morning, Ryan.

00:04:19.850 --> 00:04:22.630
Is your leg really doing okay?

00:04:22.630 --> 00:04:23.570
Yeah.

00:04:24.590 --> 00:04:26.510
{\an9}Winning Ticket

00:04:25.220 --> 00:04:26.720
No fair talking to her first, Ryan!

00:04:26.720 --> 00:04:28.920
Are you racing or something?

00:04:26.720 --> 00:04:28.640
{\an7}Nice Nature

00:04:28.920 --> 00:04:31.240
I wanted to talk to her together.

00:04:31.240 --> 00:04:32.900
You're so silly.

00:04:32.900 --> 00:04:35.120
Let's say it all together, then.

00:04:35.560 --> 00:04:36.830
One… Two…

00:04:36.830 --> 00:04:39.240
We're going to cheer you on!

00:04:41.190 --> 00:04:42.500
Thank you.

00:04:55.290 --> 00:04:57.790
{\an8}So this is the Tokyo Racecourse.

00:04:59.190 --> 00:05:01.750
They're making the final
preparations for the Japan Cup.

00:05:01.750 --> 00:05:03.960
What do you think of the Tokyo Racecourse?

00:05:03.960 --> 00:05:05.200
{\an8}It's a nice track.

00:05:05.200 --> 00:05:07.870
Are there any Japanese horse
girls that have caught your eye?

00:05:08.390 --> 00:05:10.550
{\an8}Everyone's quite cute.

00:05:15.210 --> 00:05:17.060
So she's come, after all.

00:05:17.060 --> 00:05:18.090
Yeah.

00:05:18.090 --> 00:05:20.020
Has Broye gone for a run yet?

00:05:20.020 --> 00:05:20.750
Not yet.

00:05:21.650 --> 00:05:24.180
She's not even close to worried.

00:05:30.930 --> 00:05:32.440
She's got a punch to her.

00:05:32.440 --> 00:05:34.290
Look at those muscles.

00:05:44.690 --> 00:05:46.450
She goes full speed from the start?

00:05:54.070 --> 00:05:55.210
What was her time?

00:05:55.210 --> 00:05:56.930
I don't believe it.

00:05:58.470 --> 00:05:59.580
That's…

00:05:59.930 --> 00:06:02.590
She's beaten Rudolf's time.

00:06:02.590 --> 00:06:04.710
I can't believe it.

00:06:05.130 --> 00:06:07.430
Suzuka has her comeback race soon, too.

00:06:07.430 --> 00:06:09.930
When it rains, it pours.

00:06:09.930 --> 00:06:12.860
I guess you were worried about her, too.

00:06:12.860 --> 00:06:14.650
Suzuka used to be a part of Rigil.

00:06:14.650 --> 00:06:18.610
I'm happy that she's able to race again.

00:06:18.610 --> 00:06:20.810
It's too early to be happy.

00:06:21.370 --> 00:06:25.300
You don't think Suzuka can take first?

00:06:25.300 --> 00:06:26.800
I'm not sure.

00:06:26.800 --> 00:06:28.250
Her comeback race…

00:06:28.250 --> 00:06:31.400
There's a horse girl that's been
doing well lately that'll race, too.

00:06:34.330 --> 00:06:38.040
She might be forced to face a cold reality.

00:06:36.520 --> 00:06:38.040
{\an7}Sun Visor

00:06:38.040 --> 00:06:42.770
I just like watching them race.

00:06:42.770 --> 00:06:45.210
You never lose that confidence
of yours, do you?

00:06:45.770 --> 00:06:46.570
No,

00:06:48.250 --> 00:06:49.880
I have.

00:06:58.200 --> 00:07:00.390
Suzuka, you're not going home?

00:07:00.390 --> 00:07:02.600
My race is coming up, so I
thought I'd stay a bit longer.

00:07:02.600 --> 00:07:05.070
You sure do work hard.

00:07:05.440 --> 00:07:07.340
I don't want to have any regrets.

00:07:07.340 --> 00:07:09.210
It's your comeback race, after all.

00:07:09.780 --> 00:07:11.550
Why are you laughing?

00:07:11.550 --> 00:07:13.780
I didn't expect you to be
worried for me, Air Groove.

00:07:13.780 --> 00:07:15.600
I-I'm not worried at all!

00:07:15.600 --> 00:07:17.710
Oh, is this the Japanese "tsundere"?

00:07:17.710 --> 00:07:18.330
Taiki!

00:07:19.170 --> 00:07:21.850
I want to do some bodybuilding, too!

00:07:21.850 --> 00:07:24.310
Suzuka, can I join you here?

00:07:24.310 --> 00:07:25.590
S-Sure.

00:07:25.590 --> 00:07:27.290
You're going to bother Suzuka.

00:07:27.290 --> 00:07:28.710
It's okay.

00:07:28.710 --> 00:07:30.740
Let's train together.
It's been a while.

00:07:31.260 --> 00:07:32.880
I'll train, too, I guess.

00:07:32.880 --> 00:07:34.430
Let's go get changed!

00:07:34.760 --> 00:07:36.090
Hold on a second!

00:07:38.130 --> 00:07:39.400
I can't lose this.

00:07:39.930 --> 00:07:42.280
Did you see Broye's press conference?

00:07:42.280 --> 00:07:43.440
I did!

00:07:43.440 --> 00:07:45.750
I'm going to have to go see the Japan Cup.

00:07:43.440 --> 00:07:48.150
{\an8}Will Special Week win the Japan Cup?
Sun Visor's on fire! Confident for next race
Silence Suzuka recovers, ready for comeback race!
Broye makes a bold announcement!
Broye enters Japan Cup

00:07:45.750 --> 00:07:48.150
Suzuka's having her comeback
race right before that, right?

00:07:48.150 --> 00:07:52.040
Even El Condor Pasa
couldn't beat Broye, though.

00:07:48.150 --> 00:07:54.660
{\an8}Broye, who won the Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe,
will be participating in the Japan Cup.

00:07:52.040 --> 00:07:54.660
The Tokyo Racecourse is going
to be on fire this weekend.

00:07:56.830 --> 00:07:58.830
{\an7}Broye's going to win I
thought it would be Special Week,
but… Broye's hot I think Spe-chan
has a chance, after seeing her in Tennoushou

00:08:01.120 --> 00:08:03.580
{\an9}Suzuki SP @akashi0229 18 seconds ago
Not even El Condor Pasa could bear her…
---
yuki @yamada145 23 seconds ago
I get to see Broye in real life!
---
Count Carrot VII @carrot7 30 seconds ago
No one stands a chance against Broye…

00:08:17.010 --> 00:08:18.760
{\an6}Training Regimen

00:08:47.370 --> 00:08:49.210
Good pace there.

00:08:50.360 --> 00:08:52.300
I'd like to go one more time.

00:08:52.300 --> 00:08:53.970
Suzuka-san!

00:08:54.290 --> 00:08:57.460
I can have them leave if
they're distracting you.

00:08:57.460 --> 00:08:59.210
No, I'm fine.

00:09:08.230 --> 00:09:09.520
Spe-chan…

00:09:10.020 --> 00:09:11.150
El-chan!

00:09:11.150 --> 00:09:13.240
Give me a moment of your time.

00:09:13.240 --> 00:09:13.970
Huh?

00:09:17.450 --> 00:09:18.490
El-chan.

00:09:18.490 --> 00:09:21.390
El-chan, I have to get to practice.

00:09:21.390 --> 00:09:22.080
Spe-chan…

00:09:23.370 --> 00:09:24.790
Read this.

00:09:25.460 --> 00:09:29.420
{\an8}El Condor Pasa's Winning Techniques

00:09:26.730 --> 00:09:29.420
My strategy for beating Broye is in there.

00:09:31.830 --> 00:09:33.420
All of this?

00:09:33.420 --> 00:09:37.800
Just so you know, I didn't make this for you.

00:09:38.200 --> 00:09:42.300
It's the research I did for when
I have a chance to race her again.

00:09:42.300 --> 00:09:45.540
But I want you to win.

00:09:46.760 --> 00:09:48.060
El-chan…

00:09:49.650 --> 00:09:50.990
Thank you.

00:09:50.990 --> 00:09:52.430
But I'm fine.

00:09:52.430 --> 00:09:54.570
Use this notebook for yourself.

00:09:55.970 --> 00:09:59.430
I need to win on my own.

00:10:01.940 --> 00:10:03.910
I won't forgive you if you lose.

00:10:03.910 --> 00:10:04.900
Right!

00:10:10.550 --> 00:10:13.300
Tomorrow's race is coming,
whether you want it to or not.

00:10:13.300 --> 00:10:14.550
Right.

00:10:14.550 --> 00:10:17.000
Broye is faster than I thought,

00:10:17.000 --> 00:10:19.970
and there's someone out there who's
doing well who'll be in Suzuka's race.

00:10:20.930 --> 00:10:23.290
I don't think I'll have an easy victory.

00:10:23.960 --> 00:10:25.430
Neither do I.

00:10:26.340 --> 00:10:28.640
You two have a good look in your eyes.

00:10:28.640 --> 00:10:32.040
I know that you've got a stronger fire
in you than others just by looking,

00:10:32.470 --> 00:10:33.330
but—

00:10:33.330 --> 00:10:34.410
Trainer-san!

00:10:34.410 --> 00:10:35.530
What is it, Spe?

00:10:35.850 --> 00:10:40.530
I remember what you told us
during the training camp.

00:10:40.530 --> 00:10:44.410
I want to see a race where
all of you can participate!

00:10:44.410 --> 00:10:48.220
An exciting race like we had today!

00:10:48.220 --> 00:10:50.170
Did I say that?

00:10:50.170 --> 00:10:55.450
I will never forget that you and my
mom have pinned your dreams on me!

00:10:55.450 --> 00:10:56.650
Me, neither.

00:10:58.690 --> 00:11:03.130
<i>I hope that being so into
this doesn't end up hurting them.</i>

00:11:04.850 --> 00:11:06.850
{\an7}Hello, Mom.
Tomorrow is Suzuka-san's comeback race.
Sun Visor is also doing great lately…

00:11:10.680 --> 00:11:12.180
Did I wake you?

00:11:12.610 --> 00:11:13.860
It's okay.

00:11:14.410 --> 00:11:17.480
Suzuka-san, do your best out there tomorrow.

00:11:17.480 --> 00:11:18.340
Yeah.

00:11:19.290 --> 00:11:20.850
Hey, Spe-chan…

00:11:20.850 --> 00:11:21.610
Yeah?

00:11:22.110 --> 00:11:23.350
I…

00:11:27.590 --> 00:11:29.620
I believe I can win.

00:11:29.620 --> 00:11:32.490
Yeah! I believe in you, too!

00:11:33.000 --> 00:11:37.000
{\an8}Umamusume

00:11:33.000 --> 00:11:37.000
{\an8}Pretty Derby

00:11:38.930 --> 00:11:40.970
There's so many people!

00:11:40.970 --> 00:11:43.550
This is the Open Special.

00:11:43.550 --> 00:11:45.410
I know tomorrow's the Japan Cup,

00:11:45.410 --> 00:11:48.100
but why wouldn't Spe-chan
come to cheer her on?

00:11:50.480 --> 00:11:54.980
I'm sure Spe doesn't
consider today the final goal.

00:11:55.730 --> 00:11:56.900
What does that mean?

00:11:56.900 --> 00:11:59.270
You say some good things
every once in a while.

00:11:59.270 --> 00:12:01.610
I wonder if Silence Suzuka can win.

00:12:01.610 --> 00:12:03.750
It'll be great if she can
just cross the finish line.

00:12:03.750 --> 00:12:05.780
I thought I'd never get
to see her run again.

00:12:05.780 --> 00:12:07.270
What are you saying?!

00:12:07.270 --> 00:12:09.440
Of course Suzuka-senpai is going to win!

00:12:09.440 --> 00:12:11.500
Hey, calm down.

00:12:11.500 --> 00:12:13.660
I want her to win, too.

00:12:13.660 --> 00:12:15.450
It's been a while since she's raced.

00:12:15.450 --> 00:12:16.970
All right, guys!

00:12:16.970 --> 00:12:18.420
We're going to send her our good thoughts!

00:12:19.190 --> 00:12:21.620
What's with that unscientific stuff?

00:12:19.490 --> 00:12:26.300
{\an8}Win, win, win!

00:12:19.490 --> 00:12:26.300
{\an4}Energy

00:12:21.620 --> 00:12:23.240
I'm doing it, too!

00:12:23.240 --> 00:12:26.300
Well, I guess all we can do now is pray.

00:12:26.470 --> 00:12:31.060
Win, win, win, win!

00:12:26.470 --> 00:12:31.060
{\an8}Energy

00:12:33.480 --> 00:12:34.710
Suzuka…

00:12:34.710 --> 00:12:36.190
What is it?

00:12:36.570 --> 00:12:38.890
I've been lying.

00:12:39.320 --> 00:12:41.940
Lying?

00:12:42.390 --> 00:12:45.590
If it's just a fracture, it'll heal, right?

00:12:45.590 --> 00:12:47.780
Yeah, of course.

00:12:47.780 --> 00:12:49.570
I'll be able to run, right?

00:12:50.130 --> 00:12:52.540
Yeah, well…

00:12:54.650 --> 00:12:58.840
The doctor told me you'd probably
never be able to race again.

00:13:00.180 --> 00:13:02.890
But Spe believed in you,

00:13:02.890 --> 00:13:05.000
and everyone believed in you.

00:13:05.000 --> 00:13:07.490
And today, you're racing again.

00:13:08.470 --> 00:13:09.720
That's why I…

00:13:09.720 --> 00:13:10.720
Trainer-san…

00:13:11.860 --> 00:13:13.850
I'm going to win.

00:13:16.930 --> 00:13:18.190
Right.

00:13:20.810 --> 00:13:22.400
I'll see you later.

00:13:27.210 --> 00:13:30.280
<i>Have fun running, Suzuka.</i>

00:13:30.950 --> 00:13:33.450
<i>That's all I want from you today.</i>

00:13:55.140 --> 00:13:56.810
{\an7}Let's run together! — Special
Week See you on the tracks again!
—El Condor Pasa Free food when you
get back! On the trainer. —Gold Ship

00:14:24.550 --> 00:14:26.260
<i>It's Silence Suzuka!</i>

00:14:26.260 --> 00:14:29.050
<i>Silence Suzuka has entered the track!</i>

00:14:31.640 --> 00:14:33.450
That's a loud cheer.

00:14:33.450 --> 00:14:34.470
They get to see…

00:14:34.470 --> 00:14:35.850
<i>…her run again.</i>

00:14:36.560 --> 00:14:38.180
Welcome back!

00:14:38.180 --> 00:14:39.640
We were waiting for you!

00:14:41.650 --> 00:14:45.250
Win, win, win, win!

00:14:41.650 --> 00:14:44.480
{\an8}Energy

00:14:46.210 --> 00:14:48.130
Silence Suzuka-senpai…

00:14:49.460 --> 00:14:53.120
It's the Open Special. I can't
have you taking this lightly.

00:14:50.930 --> 00:14:53.120
{\an9}Sun Visor

00:14:53.120 --> 00:14:54.970
It's been a year since you last raced.

00:14:54.970 --> 00:14:56.630
Do you really think you can win?

00:14:56.630 --> 00:14:59.370
I'm going to be the star today.

00:14:59.990 --> 00:15:03.880
<i>Sun Visor has made a declaration of war!</i>

00:15:04.260 --> 00:15:06.420
You can make all the noise you want.

00:15:06.420 --> 00:15:11.090
I'm going to win and take the
position of star horse girl.

00:15:15.100 --> 00:15:17.100
<i>Silence Suzuka has entered the gate</i>

00:15:17.100 --> 00:15:20.330
<i>to break the quiet that fell
over the track that fateful day.</i>

00:15:40.660 --> 00:15:43.530
<i>The main race today has begun!</i>

00:15:43.530 --> 00:15:46.180
<i>Silence Suzuka came out of the gates late!</i>

00:15:46.180 --> 00:15:47.930
<i>Silence Suzuka came out late!</i>

00:15:47.930 --> 00:15:50.130
<i>She's starting from the back of the pack.</i>

00:15:50.130 --> 00:15:52.970
<i>Sun Visor is in a good position.</i>

00:15:52.970 --> 00:15:55.860
<i>Seems like her time away
has caused her problems.</i>

00:15:55.860 --> 00:15:57.740
<i>I'm going to win this race!</i>

00:15:59.890 --> 00:16:01.890
<i>Suzuka…</i>

00:16:01.890 --> 00:16:03.390
<i>Sun Visor is running well.</i>

00:16:03.390 --> 00:16:04.830
<i>She's the second favorite for this race,</i>

00:16:04.830 --> 00:16:06.180
<i>but she's got the skills necessary to win.</i>

00:16:06.630 --> 00:16:07.650
<i>Of course I do.</i>

00:16:08.420 --> 00:16:11.140
<i>Silence Suzuka is having trouble at the rear.</i>

00:16:11.140 --> 00:16:13.160
<i>Maybe her accident really did hurt her.</i>

00:16:13.160 --> 00:16:15.530
<i>Silence Suzuka isn't gaining at all.</i>

00:16:15.530 --> 00:16:16.490
<i>We can do this!</i>

00:16:16.490 --> 00:16:19.690
<i>This is a different race than we
normally see from Silence Suzuka.</i>

00:16:19.690 --> 00:16:21.750
<i>It'll be difficult to come back
from this far behind.</i>

00:16:37.720 --> 00:16:39.660
She can't do it, I guess.

00:16:39.660 --> 00:16:42.100
I just hope she finishes in one piece.

00:16:42.100 --> 00:16:44.440
<i>Silence Suzuka is still in last place.</i>

00:16:44.440 --> 00:16:47.190
<i>She's having trouble running.</i>

00:16:47.190 --> 00:16:49.590
<i>I can take this last stretch.</i>

00:16:49.590 --> 00:16:52.820
<i>I guess Silence Suzuka couldn't
live up to all those rumors!</i>

00:17:10.920 --> 00:17:12.460
She's finally made her move!

00:17:13.720 --> 00:17:16.130
That sure was unnerving.

00:17:18.390 --> 00:17:20.850
Go, Suzuka!

00:17:20.850 --> 00:17:23.530
We can't…

00:17:24.100 --> 00:17:25.850
We can't…

00:17:25.850 --> 00:17:27.310
Suzuka-san!

00:17:27.310 --> 00:17:30.020
You can run faster, Suzuka!

00:17:30.340 --> 00:17:33.030
We can't…

00:17:33.030 --> 00:17:34.780
Suzuka!

00:17:34.780 --> 00:17:36.770
<i>Everyone here at the track is cheering—</i>

00:17:36.770 --> 00:17:38.900
<i>Silence Suzuka has made her way up!</i>

00:17:38.900 --> 00:17:41.610
<i>Silence Suzuka has finally awoken!</i>

00:17:41.610 --> 00:17:42.540
<i>Silence Suzuka…</i>

00:17:42.540 --> 00:17:45.500
…keeps passing one girl after another!

00:17:45.500 --> 00:17:46.580
Run, Suzuka!

00:17:53.780 --> 00:17:55.350
<i>No way…</i>

00:17:57.750 --> 00:17:58.720
<i>She's fast!</i>

00:17:58.720 --> 00:18:00.390
<i>I can't believe it!</i>

00:18:00.390 --> 00:18:03.410
Silence Suzuka has passed Sun Visor!

00:18:03.410 --> 00:18:03.890
Silence Suzuka…

00:18:03.890 --> 00:18:06.210
<i>…has left everyone behind,</i>

00:18:06.210 --> 00:18:07.870
<i>and is now in first!</i>

00:18:07.870 --> 00:18:09.150
<i>I won't let you!</i>

00:18:10.950 --> 00:18:12.610
<i>I don't believe it!</i>

00:18:12.610 --> 00:18:14.170
<i>She's sped up even more!</i>

00:18:14.170 --> 00:18:16.830
<i>Silence Suzuka has a huge lead!</i>

00:18:16.830 --> 00:18:19.660
<i>So this is Silence Suzuka.</i>

00:18:20.410 --> 00:18:23.010
Wow, she was able to come
back from so far behind!

00:18:23.010 --> 00:18:25.080
Suzuka-senpai's so awesome!

00:18:25.080 --> 00:18:26.740
Go!

00:18:26.740 --> 00:18:28.810
I wanna show Spe this!

00:18:28.810 --> 00:18:31.460
We'll have plenty of chances to see this!

00:18:34.090 --> 00:18:37.500
Her ability is going to be a threat to Rigil.

00:18:37.500 --> 00:18:38.300
Yeah.

00:18:38.300 --> 00:18:40.190
I want to run with her again.

00:18:40.190 --> 00:18:41.880
She's standing out more than me.

00:18:41.880 --> 00:18:43.180
I want to race her!

00:18:43.180 --> 00:18:45.930
<i>Silence Suzuka is in first!</i>

00:18:46.310 --> 00:18:48.020
Silence Suzuka…

00:18:48.020 --> 00:18:50.010
<i>…has crossed the finish line in first place!</i>

00:18:55.110 --> 00:18:57.560
Welcome back, Suzuka-san.

00:18:58.100 --> 00:18:59.650
<i>I'll do the same tomorrow!</i>

00:19:02.660 --> 00:19:06.290
<i>Silence Suzuka has made a miraculous return!</i>

00:19:06.850 --> 00:19:09.830
She won with such a huge lead.

00:19:09.830 --> 00:19:12.170
She tied the record and won hands down.

00:19:12.170 --> 00:19:13.410
She ran great out there,

00:19:13.410 --> 00:19:15.840
but I'm moved by her mental strength.

00:19:15.840 --> 00:19:18.090
That was a wonderful comeback performance.

00:19:19.340 --> 00:19:23.180
{\an8}Silence Suzuka
Welcome Back!

00:19:29.330 --> 00:19:32.710
{\an8}I'll have to put on an even better
performance tomorrow.

00:19:40.970 --> 00:19:42.890
I won't say congratulations.

00:19:42.890 --> 00:19:45.160
I'm going to win next time.

00:19:50.080 --> 00:19:53.290
Please run with me again someday.

00:19:54.250 --> 00:19:56.490
Yes, let's run again.

00:20:03.330 --> 00:20:04.900
Hey!

00:20:23.280 --> 00:20:25.780
All right, let's celebrate Suzuka's win!

00:20:25.780 --> 00:20:27.410
{\an8}Give me your hands—

00:20:26.550 --> 00:20:29.430
Suzuka-senpai, I was moved out there!

00:20:29.430 --> 00:20:30.290
Thank you.

00:20:30.290 --> 00:20:32.290
You were crying a bit, weren't you?

00:20:32.830 --> 00:20:35.210
{\an8}What are you talking about?!

00:20:33.170 --> 00:20:35.210
Our trainer sure was crying.

00:20:35.210 --> 00:20:36.680
Our trainer was?

00:20:36.680 --> 00:20:38.570
We'll have to tease him a bit.

00:20:43.190 --> 00:20:44.470
That was good.

00:20:44.470 --> 00:20:45.570
Thanks.

00:20:45.570 --> 00:20:46.940
You're not going to join them?

00:20:46.940 --> 00:20:49.890
I'll leave the noise-making to them.

00:20:50.210 --> 00:20:52.800
What magic did you use?

00:20:52.800 --> 00:20:53.960
I didn't do a thing.

00:20:53.960 --> 00:20:57.560
But you were so confident
the last time we talked.

00:20:58.250 --> 00:20:59.900
You think so?

00:20:59.900 --> 00:21:00.320
Huh?

00:21:03.060 --> 00:21:06.000
She won by her own strength.

00:21:06.000 --> 00:21:08.170
I couldn't do a thing for her.

00:21:11.210 --> 00:21:13.540
I didn't think you'd take first.

00:21:14.390 --> 00:21:15.830
Trainer-san…

00:21:15.830 --> 00:21:17.130
Hmm?

00:21:17.130 --> 00:21:19.350
Is it true you were crying?

00:21:19.960 --> 00:21:22.090
I-I wasn't crying!

00:21:23.730 --> 00:21:24.690
What is it?

00:21:25.340 --> 00:21:28.470
I'll be counting on you in the future.

00:21:32.180 --> 00:21:35.290
Wait. Are you crying?

00:21:35.290 --> 00:21:38.190
N-No, I'm not. Jeez…

00:21:39.220 --> 00:21:40.160
This is where it starts.

00:21:40.160 --> 00:21:40.840
Huh?

00:21:41.490 --> 00:21:44.190
I'm going to make my dream come true.

00:21:44.600 --> 00:21:45.690
And…

00:21:45.690 --> 00:21:49.620
I'm going to keep running
and keep my promise.

00:21:58.470 --> 00:22:01.240
<i>I'm going to keep my promise.</i>

00:22:04.260 --> 00:22:07.340
<i>I'm going to become the
best horse girl in Japan.</i>

00:22:12.350 --> 00:22:15.730
<i>All the horse girls have entered
their respective gates.</i>

00:22:16.630 --> 00:22:20.100
<i>It's finally time for the Japan Cup!</i>

00:22:25.690 --> 00:22:28.850
In a dash, in a flash,
just a little more now,

00:22:28.760 --> 00:22:31.590
each new race like a dream neverending

00:22:31.470 --> 00:22:34.400
Every one of us will blaze a
trail aimed right for the stars

00:22:34.280 --> 00:22:39.450
Together we'll run! Let's
go! Our starting gate!

00:22:48.580 --> 00:22:54.030
With curiosity in hand, go tug
on tomorrow's tail and say hello

00:22:53.910 --> 00:22:58.910
It's right there, so go on and close
the gap now (Right here and now!)

00:22:59.620 --> 00:23:05.100
Can't play by the rules they tell
you! Gotta learn it all by experience!

00:23:05.000 --> 00:23:09.940
If we just plan to run for the
end, everything will turn out okay!

00:23:10.100 --> 00:23:13.970
Can't get me down,
hesitate, or go too slowly!

00:23:15.720 --> 00:23:19.690
We know that deep in our hearts is a song

00:23:19.770 --> 00:23:22.910
that sings "give it your all"! Make it shine!

00:23:23.490 --> 00:23:26.850
In a dash, in a flash, just a
little more now, (Dash! Dash!)

00:23:26.710 --> 00:23:29.590
every step like the wind
neverending (Zoom! Zoom!)

00:23:29.460 --> 00:23:32.510
A twinkling star that we wear
on our sleeves (But only one!)

00:23:32.360 --> 00:23:34.780
Let's let our hearts race
together as one! (Grow up! Shine!)

00:23:34.660 --> 00:23:37.910
One more step, one more push,
just a little more now, (Dash! Dash!)

00:23:37.790 --> 00:23:40.550
each new race like a dream
neverending (Zoom! Zoom!)

00:23:40.440 --> 00:23:43.310
Every one of us will see
our path to the very end!

00:23:43.290 --> 00:23:49.020
Let's run now, everyone!
Let's go! Our starting gate!

